text: I'm Bonnie Faulkner. Today we're featuring Michael C. Rupert, publisher and editor of From the Wilderness Publications on The Truth and Lies of 9-11. The following is from a presentation Rupert gave on February 21st in San Francisco. This is the seventh lecture that I have given in the 9-11 series. I want to leave you tonight with the message that your lives and your liberty are on the line now. There is no more opportunity for armchair discussion. There is no more time. The philosophy with which I started publishing From the Wilderness four years ago was very simple. I don't publish anything that I can't document. I don't ask you to take anything that I write on faith. I will offer opinions and I'll tell you their opinions. I'll give you my analysis. But I don't make any assertions unless I tell you where I got the information so that you can go find it for yourself. And I have taken on some very big issues. I've been in the business of big names in four years. I won't go through the litany. I have never been sued because truth is an absolute defense against libel. Absolutely. All the time. They're irrelevant. Which is what George Bush sells. I have to shake their belief in the system. You don't do that with speculation.
